  <Subject Subject_ID="300259605">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300008509</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>retirement communities [300008509], settlements by occupants [300008502], inhabited places [300008347], Settlements and Landscapes (hierarchy name) [300008346], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Retirement communities providing a full range of personal care and supplemental services, often including transportation, medicine, recreational facilities, and financial advice. Distinguished from "life care communities" by charging monthly fees that can vary over the duration of the residency, instead of a one-time up-front charge.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para designar comunidades de retiro que proporcionan una gama completa de cuidados personales y servicios suplementarios, incluyendo con frecuencia transporte, medicinas, prestaciones recreativas y asesoramiento financiero. Se diferencia de "residencia de la tercera edad” en el cargo de las tarifas mensuales que pueden variar durante el tiempo que dure la residencia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor woongemeenschappen voor gepensioneerde mensen die volledige persoonlijke zorg en aanvullende diensten ontvangen, vaak inclusief vervoer, medicatie, recreatieve faciliteiten en financieel advies. Te onderscheiden van 'life care communities', omdat er een maandelijkse vergoeding wordt gevraagd die afhankelijk is van de verblijfsduur en geen eenmalige vergoeding vooraf.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>提供全面性個人照護及輔助服務的退休社區，照護與服務內容多包括交通接送、醫療、休閒設施、財務規畫諮詢等。與「生活照護社區」不同之處在於，入住此類社區的費用係每月支付，費率可能依居住時間長短有所不同，並非一次付清。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
